long_desc.thetext:
Another episode in the vein of bug 402237:
Running AmbiguousMethodTest with -Dcompliance=1.8 -Drun.javac=enabled -Djdk.root=<location of jdk1.8.0/ea-lambda-b81> reports 11 deviations, which should be investigated:
Eclipse found error(s) but Javac did not find any: - test010a()
Eclipse/Javac standard error mismatch - test028() - test029() - test031() - test037() - test038() - test042()
Eclipse found warning(s) but Javac did not find any - test075()
Javac found error(s) but Eclipse did not find any - test081() - test082() - test083()

(In reply to comment #0) > Javac found error(s) but Eclipse did not find any > - test081() > - test082() > - test083()
When addressing these, see also disabled tests InterfaceMethodTest._testBridge03/04() from bug 391376, which are in fact variants of the above test081().

(In reply to Stephan Herrmann from comment #0) On a b126, here is the list:
Unused Excuse test028 test029 test031 test037 test038 test042
Eclipse found warning(s) but Javac did not find any test075
JavaC found errors Eclipse only warnings test074 test051 test053
JavaC found errors, Eclipse did not find any
test081 test082 test083

(In reply to Manoj Palat from comment #2) Thanks!
> Unused Excuse > test028 > test029 > test031 > test037 > test038 > test042
If javac bugs got fixed we should update that excuse to indicate that it is no longer used for 1.8.
> JavaC found errors Eclipse only warnings > test074 > test051 > test053
Those are some of the trouble makers from bug 423505. I actually have an idea what might make the difference. Otherwise I need to check on the EG list...

(In reply to Stephan Herrmann from comment #3)
> > Unused Excuse > > test028 > > test029 > > test031 > > test037 > > test038 > > test042
All due to JavacBug6294779 which got fixed; commit: http://git.eclipse.org/c/jdt/eclipse.jdt.core.git/commit/?h=BETA_JAVA8&id=d135b079aa3cba8ba7f809e3b8fa111052de185d
*** Bug 422896 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
*** Bug 402237 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***

Created attachment 239760 Failure List
Difference set of javac compatibility failures: |{1.8 with b126} - {1.7 with 7u51}| = 160

Created attachment 239926 Proposed Patch
contains new excuses, modifications to existing excuses, and new runNegative/conformance tests to accommodate javac comparisons.
Todo: cleanup and reduce these runNegative/conformance functions to an optimum number.
Created attachment 239927 Failure List with summary of actions taken in the patch

(In reply to Manoj Palat from comment #9) > Created attachment 239927 [details] > Failure List with summary of actions taken in the patch
To be looked at in phases in post 4.5
